parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down, lose power, or experience electrical malfunctions, which can lead to accidents, fires, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical malfunctions
shuts down
or loses power; warning messages appear on the dashboard; the vehicle is unable to charge; the charging system is unable to operate at full capacity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the charging system can cause the vehicle to not charge properly, leading to reduced range, increased charging time, or even fires.
symptoms: The vehicle is unable to charge; the charging system is unable to operate at full capacity; the charging port has failed and needs to be replaced; lights flicker in the home when charging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery control module can cause the vehicle to shut down, lose power, or experience electrical malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical malfunctions
shuts down
or loses power; warning messages appear on the dashboard; the vehicle is unable to charge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the safety handles can cause the vehicle to be unsafe to drive, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The safety handles are missing or not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches forward unexpectedly
even when the driver's foot is on the brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rearview camera can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rearview camera display shows a blank screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the trunk sensor can cause the trunk to close unexpectedly, leading to injuries or accidents.
symptoms: The trunk closes unexpectedly
even when the driver is not attempting to close it.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress through the sunroof can cause damage to the vehicle's interior, electrical systems, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Water leaking into the vehicle through the sunroof
sunroof exploding or shattering without warning
glass shards falling while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable activation of the tailgate sensor can cause injury to individuals standing near the vehicle or lead to accidents.
symptoms: Tailgate closing unexpectedly while loading or unloading items
requiring quick action to avoid injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A potentially critical self-discharge condition can lead to thermal overload, smoke, or fire, increasing the risk of a fire.
symptoms: Loss of range and/or performance
high-voltage battery overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden and uncontrollable acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Spontaneous acceleration
spinning of the vehicle
collision with other objects or vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause damage to the vehicle's interior, electrical systems, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Leather dashboard warping due to water ingress.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate brake hold function can cause the vehicle to roll forward or backward unexpectedly, even when in drive or reverse, which can lead to accidents, especially on inclines or hills.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls forward or backward when the accelerator is released and the vehicle is not at a complete stop
the vehicle does not brake hold when in drive or reverse
the vehicle will roll in either direction regardless of the selected gear
the vehicle will roll rapidly on inclines or hills.
